entries.meaning: (Ireland, derogatory) An arrogant lower-class person, especially in Dublin.
examples: A buckeen, a jackeen, a squireen, or any of the intermediate classes.

entries.meaning: (Ireland, derogatory) Synonym of Dubliner, especially (obsolete or historical) an excessively Anglophile one.
examples: To the sellers in the market, to the barmen and barmaids, to the beggars who importuned him for a lob Mr Dedalus told the same tale, that he was an old Corkonian, that he had been trying for thirty years to get rid of his Cork accent up in Dublin and that Peter Pickakafax beside him was his eldest son but that he was only a Dublin jackeen.
